#: ../source/reference/operator/aggregation/currentOp.txt:20
msgid ""
"Returns a stream of documents containing information on active and/or "
"dormant operations for the MongoDB deployment. To run "
":pipeline:`$currentOp`, use the :method:`db.aggregate()` helper on the "
"``admin`` database."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/reference/operator/aggregation/currentOp.txt:25
msgid ""
":pipeline:`$currentOp` offers a better alternative to the "
":dbcommand:`currentOp` command and the :method:`db.currentOp` method. The"
" latter two commands are limited to returning all operations in a single "
"document, which must not exceed the maximum 16MB BSON size. Since "
":pipeline:`$currentOp` pipelines return a cursor, they are not subject to"
" these limitations."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/reference/operator/aggregation/currentOp.txt:32
msgid ""
":pipeline:`$currentOp` also enables you to perform arbitrary "
"transformations of the results as the documents pass through the "
"pipeline."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/reference/operator/aggregation/currentOp.txt:36
msgid ":pipeline:`$currentOp` takes an options document as its operand."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/reference/operator/aggregation/currentOp.txt:42
msgid "Specify an empty document to use the default values."
msgstr ""

